Measure of how closely your ranking of the athletes, based on your scores, matches the final ranking based on the total score. This ranges from -1 to 1, where 1 represents your ranking always matches the final ranking, -1 represents your ranking is always the reverse of the final ranking, 0 implies no relation between your ranking and the final ranking. The best referees have a value above 0.9, good referees have scores between 0.8 and 0.9, scores below 0.7 imply work is needed to understand which athletes are best.  

NOTE: This ranking is influenced by the other referees in your ring and which divisions you refereed. Color belts division tend to have lower correlation due to the added messiness of their poomsae. The more divisions and the more other referees you score with, the more weight should be given this value. 